{
  "stem": "3360.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A very good example of the failure of that was this ship full of Jews who went to Cuba and then were-- and had paid very large sums of money to the Cuban government and then were refused entry.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was either-- it was probably in early 1939 also-- and then eventually, were refused entry here, tried to dock here.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in our own home, then, we had an affidavit.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had to wait until our quota number would be called.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so my mother and father and I, you know, we're-- I was still going to school.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father was, really, almost unable to make any kind of a living anymore.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- excuse me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My mother had an inheritance that kind of kept us going, that was still coming in.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But there was nothing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was waiting.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was waiting to start a new life, more or less.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And less and less, a man-- a person who looked what you could call Jewish or Semitic, you know, could less and less, really show themselves out in the street.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were wanton attacks after the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so it was a matter of waiting for the time when we could leave.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And in the meantime, my other relatives, the Rothenburgs, had to move out of their-- out of their co-op apartment because it was being cleared of Jews, even though it was their own apartment that they had paid for.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they had to move into another smaller apartment, less desirable, but whatever.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And it was at that apartment that we spent our last night.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because our stuff was packed, and our furniture was sold.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
